instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands are issued from the UE5 digital‑twin interface (or other DT services) and sent to Eclipse Ditto over a WebSocket channel. Ditto forwards each command to the appropriate physical device through Eclipse Hono, which communicates with the device using the device’s native protocol (as defined in the BIM‑derived metadata). After the device executes the command, it returns a confirmation message to Ditto; only upon receiving this acknowledgement does the DT update the twin’s state. Command formats and allowed operations are derived from the device metadata extracted during deployment, and the framework ensures that only authorized services can invoke these command APIs."
