    base:desc "The technical infrastructure consists of Eclipse Hono as the IoT protocol gateway and Eclipse Ditto as the digital‑twin state repository. Physical devices connect to Hono using MQTT/HTTP (the protocols supported by Hono). The DT client (UE5) receives initial device values via an HTTP POST request and then establishes a persistent WebSocket connection to Ditto for bidirectional real‑time data exchange and command transmission. This hub‑spoke topology places Hono/Ditto as the central hub linking all physical endpoints and the visualization layer. Specific bandwidth, latency, reliability, redundancy, or security mechanisms are not detailed in the provided documents."
]

